The paper deals with the problem of agnostic Q-learning with function approximation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses sample complexity and approximation error, which are important concepts in statistical learning theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses concepts from high-dimensional statistics and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
